==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pasture
<hw>Pas"ture</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>pasture</ets>, F. <ets>p⟦acir⟧ture</ets>, L. <ets>pastura</ets>,
fr. <ets>pascere</ets>, <ets>pastum</ets>, to pasture, to feed. See
<er>Pastor</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Food; nourishment.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Toads and frogs his <qex>pasture</qex> poisonous.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Specifically: Grass growing for the food of cattle;
the food of cattle taken by grazing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Grass land for cattle, horses, etc.;
pasturage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He maketh me to lie down in green <qex>pastures</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Ps. xxiii. 2.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So graze as you find <qex>pasture</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pasture</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pasture
<hw>Pas"ture</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Pastured</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Pasturing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To feed, esp. to feed on
